-- Chevron Should Face New Trial Over Nigerian Beatings, Appeals Court Told
-- Karen Gullo
-- 2010-06-14T17:43:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-14/chevron-should-face-new-trial-over-nigerian-beatings-appeals-court-told.html

          
          
             Chevron Corp. should face a new
trial for allegedly sanctioning beatings and shootings of
Nigerian protesters in 1998 because jurors who cleared the
company in 2008 were given erroneous instructions, lawyers
for protesters told a federal appeals court in San Francisco
today.  
